article_title: Families Provide DNA to Aid MH17 Victims' Identification
article_text:
PUTRAJAYA, Malaysia—Most of the Malaysian families of those who died on Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 gave DNA samples and descriptions of their loved ones to Malaysian police on Tuesday in the first stage of a painful identification process.

The forensic police work began just before a train from the crash site carrying 251 bodies and an additional 86 body parts arrived in Kharkiv in northeastern Ukraine. Arrangements are being made...
